projects:
[{'title': 'Workshop on Conflict Sensitive Business Practices (CSBP) in Colombia', 'date': {'start': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}}, 'description': 'A two-day workshop for Dutch companies, NGOs, AgentschapNL and colleagues within the Ministry of Foreign Affairs focusing on risk and conflict management. Central to this workshop were two questions:

1. How is a company affected by external risks such as conflicts?
2. How can a company have a positive or negative impact on external conflicts?

I was responsible for the logistical part of the organisation, namely approaching Dutch companies doing business in Colombia (or interested in doing so), NGOs and colleagues of both AgentschapNL and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and inviting them to take part in the workshop. Also, I acted as a primary contact for all attendees and International Alert, the NGO that gave the workshop on conflict sensitive business practices (CSBP).
